trace.verification_evidence:
{
  "red_failure_evidence": "BEFORE THIS CELL: the Herdr trait had five methods (snapshot, ping, read_pane, send_input, send_keys) and no way to create anything at all — git show HEAD:src/herdr/mod.rs shows a trait with no create verb, so the gateway could observe herdr's workspaces but never add a tab to one. FakeHerdr's snapshot was fixed seed data that no call could grow. PRE-CHANGE CHECK THAT FAILED: cargo test --quiet --lib -- tabcreate_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([4-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed' on the untouched tree printed 'running 0 tests / test result: ok. 0 passed; 180 filtered out' and the guard grep exited 1 — no test carrying the tabcreate_ prefix existed, so the verify could not pass on an already-green suite. A second red was recorded during orchestrator review: the first implementation had FakeHerdr return WorkspaceNotFound with the requested workspace_id filled in while SocketHerdr returned it empty, so the fake was strictly kinder than the real path and no test could see the difference.",
  "green_evidence": {
    "command": "cargo test --quiet && cargo fmt --all --check && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test --lib -- tabcreate_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([4-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed'",
    "run_by": "orchestrator, independently, after the worker reported",
    "output": "cargo test --quiet: 186 passed, 0 failed (180 before this cell). fmt --all --check: silent. clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings: silent. tabcreate_-only: test result: ok. 6 passed; 0 failed; 180 filtered out. Guard grep exit code: 0."
  },
  "behavior_change_description": "The port gained tab_create on the trait, on SocketHerdr and on FakeHerdr. The socket path sends exactly workspace_id, cwd and focus:false — the explicit cwd required by D5 and the non-stealing focus required by D6 — with no label and no env key, and returns the new tab id and root pane id read off the tab_created envelope. The fake genuinely creates: it appends the Tab, the Pane carrying the requested cwd in both cwd and foreground_cwd, the PaneLayout row naming the new pane focused, and a screens entry, all under the snapshot lock, leaving the workspace's own active_tab_id untouched because focus is false.",
  "observable_difference": "A caller can now create a plain shell tab in a chosen workspace and immediately read its pane. Before, no such call existed on any implementation.",
  "regression_guard": "tabcreate_fake_appends_tab_pane_layout_and_screen asserts all four appended pieces plus that active_tab_id did not move; tabcreate_created_pane_is_readable guards the screens entry specifically, which is the piece whose absence would make read_pane fail on a pane that was just created; tabcreate_params_carry_workspace_cwd_and_focus_false pins the emitted params to exactly three keys so a later label/env addition cannot slip in silently; tabcreate_error_attaches_caller_workspace_id and tabcreate_error_other_variants_pass_through_unchanged guard the error mapping in both directions.",
  "reviewer_note": "Caught during orchestrator review and fixed before capping: parse_response deliberately leaves WorkspaceNotFound.workspace_id empty for the owning create method to fill, and nothing filled it, so against real herdr the operator saw 'workspace not found:' with a blank id while the fake showed the id correctly. The fake was nicer than the thing it stands in for and the suite could not see the gap. SocketHerdr::tab_create now runs the error through a pure attach_workspace_id mapping, tested without standing up a socket. Separately, the worker initially placed the TabCreated result type in wire.rs, outside this cell's declared files, then caught it and reverted before reporting."
}
